<dl id="n11129i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n11" href="#n11129i">N11 (VI.B.5)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n11all.htm#n11129i"> 129(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font color="green">[tribunal of penance]</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Souvent assis dans une &eacute;glise peu fr&eacute;quent&eacute;e, je passais des heures enti&egrave;res en m&eacute;ditation. Je voyais de pauvres femmes venir se prosterner devant le Tr&egrave;s-Haut, ou des p&eacute;cheurs s&apos;agenouiller au <mark>tribunal de la p&eacute;nitence</mark>. Nul ne sortait de ces lieux sans un visage plus serein <br><font color="green">[Often seated in a little frequented church I would spend whole hours in meditation. I would see poor women come and prostrate themselves before the Most-High, or sinners kneeling at the confessional. No one left those places but with a more serene face.]</font> <small> Chateaubriand, <a name="CHBD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CHBD"><cite title="source">&OElig;uvres choisies illustr&eacute;es</cite></a> (1912) I, <i>Ren&eacute;</i> 93</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
